snippet.title: Justice for Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
A recently released audio recording of Actress Amber Heard admitting to her abuse of Actor Johnny Depp during their relationship sheds much-needed light on the plight of male victims of domestic violence. 

National Domestic Violence Hotline
Advocates are available 24/7 at 1-800-799-SAFE (7233) in more than 200 languages. All calls are free and confidential.

https://malesurvivor.org/
Provides resources to male survivors of sexual trauma.

https://www.safeaustin.org/
Provides services and shelter for male victims of sexual assault and domestic violence. They can help you locate shelters in your area, where available.

snippet.title: Self Care and Mental Wellness with Amber Lee Forrester
snippet.description:
Life, Career, & Biz Coach Amber Lee Forrester share tips, advice, and resources for around Self-Care and Mental Wellness. The topic of the Lunch and Learn was specifically curated to help participants cope with stress and manage these unprecedented times.

Many of us feel that putting ourselves first is selfish, yet we also know that we can’t pour from an empty cup. Self-Care is not selfish. Self-Care is healthcare. This is what self-love looks like!

Watch this video to hear tips and techniques to:
- become more intentional about prioritizing your self-care
- develop a self-care routine that speaks to your mental wellness (that you will actually follow)
- create a foundational launchpad to recalibrate for 2021

snippet.title: NCF-248 Data Forensics and Cyber Education
snippet.description: On today's show, our host Abe Thompson talks with Amber Schroader on the world of data forensics and the impotence of having more women in cybersecurity. In an age of continuously generated data and diminishing privacy, it's essential to educate ourselves on where our information goes. As a prominent female in the cyber industry, Amber Schroader has done a lot for educating the next generation of women in cyber, whether for personal online safety or as a full-on career. Listen in as we discuss creating the future of women in cybersecurity on NCF.

snippet.title: Amber's Open Relationship with her Wife Isn't Working
snippet.description:
Amber and her wife started out in an open relationship but when she recently hooked up with a guy, it didn't go over so well. Where did she meet the guy? What exactly went down between them? How did her wife react and how did she feel about the hook up? Is she still seeing him and if so, does her wife know about it? Tune in to find out plus hear all about Amber's crazy past which include she overcame both a heroin and alcohol addiction, how she use to hook up with guys and how she eventually realized she was homoromatic (she explains what that means) and started hooking up with women, how she came out of the closet and how her parents took the news, and a whole lot more.

snippet.title: Are the RDAs relevant on a keto/carnivore diet? A conversation with Amber O’Hearn.
snippet.description:
L. Amber O’Hearn is a data scientist by profession with a background in math, computer science, linguistics, and psychology. She has been studying and experimenting with low-carb, ketogenic diets since 1997, and more recently writing and speaking about her findings. Her review on the evolutionary appropriateness and benefit of weaning babies onto a meat-based, high fat, low carb diet, was included as testimony defending Professor Tim Noakes in his recent trial.  Amber has been eating a plant-free diet since 2009.

Time stamps: 

4:03 Amber O'Hearn's love of singing.
6:03 Amber's journey towards carnivore.
11:50 Pitfalls of bipolar medications.
13:50 Finding the carnivore community (zeroing in on health).
16:03 Amber's amazing mood improvements.
17:19 Had Amber tried re-introducing plants back into her diet?
18:10 The fear of losing variety in your diet.
20:13 How to cook brain.
20:47 Salmonella.
21:43 Eating raw animal foods and food safety.
23:06 Why eating egg whites may not be a good idea.
25:00 How Amber's mood became substantially more stable.
27:49 Micronutrients in meat.
29:00 Unique nutrients in animal foods.
31:34 Eliminating plants from the diet.
33:18 Carnivory and diet dogmatism.
34:25 Humans as facultative carnivores.
37:21 Bioavailability of nutrients in animal vs. plant foods.
40:33 Fiber.
41:33 Other nutrients that low carb dieters do not need as much of. (Vitamin c and scurvy.)
43:13 Linus Pauling's theory.
50:06 Iodine.
50:57 Is the carnivore diet safe for children?
54:00 Newborns/infants and ketosis.
56:27 Ketones and cholesterol.
58:41 Ketones and improved working memory/other benefits.
59:53 Fat to protein ratio on a carnivore diet.
1:06:20 The effect of protein on insulin.
1:09:22 Does protein really have calories?
1:13:12 Information on where to find Amber online and her upcoming work.

snippet.title: Carnivore for Healing 2 0
snippet.description:
This fun interview with Amber from @lonestarketogirl will inspire you on your weight loss journey and help you shift your mindsets to ENJOY your journey! Amber has lost 62 lbs. and counting and has gone from a size 24 to a size 2 on her journey with keto and carnivore!

We talk about
- why skinny doesn’t mean healthy
- how weight loss comes through health and NOT health through weight loss
- how carnivore helped Amber find healing 2.0
- why ditching the scale was the strategy she needed
- and so much more!

Plus be sure to checkout Amber’s Emotional Eating Quiz here: https://amberapproved.ca/emotional-eating-quiz/ 

  

  Enjoy and let us know your thoughts as we love hearing from this community!

snippet.title: Y.LO Epicure catering talks to the Colorado Women's Chamber of Commerce about helping the community!
snippet.description:
Working together is the key! Colorado Women's Chamber of Commerce  (CWCC) is in the house!  

Your Colorado Chamber's are hard at work creating awareness for local businesses in the community just like Y.Lo Epicure Catering!

Tune in to meet Kristen Blessman and Morgan Montgomery from the CWCC! They're doing a great job for our community and it's time to hear all about it!

A local catering company Y.Lo Epicure is here too, and owner Lisa Altenburg is here not only to show off some of their awesome food, but talk about their relationship with the CWCC!

Your culinary career starts today, and it's FREE! All you have to do is get signed up at themoderneater.com and click on the Emily Griffith Culinary Quick Start tab to get signed up!

Lulu Lantzy from the Culinary Quick Start program is here to talk about how they work closely with the Colorado Chamber's and the community to turn their culinary students into the culinary work force!

snippet.title: Using Peptide Therapy to Reverse Autoimmune Disease, Hormone Imbalances & Low Energy with Dr. Amber
snippet.description:
Peptide therapy is a little-known new emerging treatment in regenerative medicine  that you can do at home to send autoimmune disease into remission, heal chronic pain, boost libido, balance hormones and optimize sleep. Dr. Amber shares all-you-need-to-know about the power of peptides and how to get started.

Bio:

Dr. Amber is a Licensed Naturopathic Doctor at MetroMD Institute of Regenerative Medicine in Los Angeles, CA. She is trained in regenerative medicine, detoxification protocols, hormone testing and treatment, bioidentical hormone therapy, peptide therapy and IV nutrient therapy. She also has a practice in Redondo Beach, CA where she specializes in bioidentical hormones and peptide therapy. Dr. Amber is a member of the International Peptide Society (IPS) and has completed peptide therapy certification training through the American Academy of Anti-aging (A4M).

Website link: www.drambernd.com

snippet.title: Panel on Black Feminism
snippet.description: GSAT Co-founder Julinna Oxley and founding member Amber Knowles joined Brianna Martin and Talisa Effinger of Coastal Carolina University for a discussion on black feminism. Brianna is a Sociology major with a focus on Social Justice, and is involved in many campus organizations. Talisa is a Black womanist from a small town in Central Virginia. She is a senior Sociology major with a concentration in Social Justice and a minor in Women's and Gender Studies. She describes herself as a mix between Angela Davis and Freddie Mercury. We are excited to get to know them better!

snippet.title: Chronic stress, inflammation and hormone balance | Season 1 Ep. 39
snippet.description:
Interview with Dr. Amber Krogsrud. Dr. Amber Krogsrud is a Naturopathic Doctor who focuses in Holistic Hormone Health. Prior to her undergraduate studies, she worked in an chiropractic clinic and discovered the beauty of natural medicine. She also developed a passion for nutrition and began pursuing a career that viewed health as a holistic lifestyle involving food as nutrition. To convert this passion to a career, Dr. Amber completed a four year medical degree at the prestigious Bastyr University in San Diego, California.

In this podcast episode you will learn:
- What a naturopathic doctor focuses on
- What indicators in your body show stress levels
- The negative effects of stress on your health
- The three phases of stress
- The antagonists cortisol and melatonin
- How physical health impacts mental health and vice versa

Enjoy listening.

With gratitude,
Julia

The Millionaire Fastlane, MJ DeMarco
